---
description: JavaScript and React quality defaults
globs: **/*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: false
---

# JS/React Quality

- Prefer functional React components and hooks.
- Keep modules small, isolated, and reusable.
- Avoid cross-import coupling across unrelated features.
- Use self-explanatory naming and structure; comments are discouraged by default.
- Enforce accessibility basics:
  - alt text for images
  - semantic elements/ARIA when needed
  - maintain readable contrast
- Keep styling and UX polished, consistent, and production-grade.
- Avoid visible provenance traces in UI copy, component names, class names, or content.

# Validation

- If scripts exist, run lint/test/build before proposing production readiness.
